    "description_long": "This object consists of a black, hexagonal coffin with gold and red trim, resting on a patch of green grass. Behind the coffin stands a large, gray stone cross with a rough, chiseled texture, serving as a grave marker. The coffin appears to be made of wood or a similar material, with a painted or lacquered finish, and is likely hollow inside. The cross is solid and robust, with a simple, blocky design and no visible inscriptions or engravings. The entire scene is set on a square base of grass, suggesting a grave plot in a cemetery or graveyard. The visual contrast between the dark coffin and the pale stone cross creates a somber, respectful atmosphere.",
